==Hindi==
===Etymology===
Ap. Prakrit कक्खहं, Prakrit कक्खे and Sanskrit कक्षं

===Postposition===
'''को''' (ko)

# [[to]]
# up to
# [[for]]
# in, on
# at
# near, on the point of

===Usage===
को marks the dative and accusative. 
It can be used as a postfix similar to -wards (e.g. ūpar-ko, 'upwards'; āge-ko, 'afterwards').

===Other dialects===
Braj कौ kau
Dakkhanī kū 
